cff-version: 1.2.0
title: >-
  Causal Network Map: interactive viewer and replication package for
  "Qualitative Shock Mapping for Quantitative Production Network Models:
  Evidence from Iran-Related Hostilities"
message: >-
  If you use this software or data, please cite the accompanying
  article and this archive.
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Kim
    given-names: Wonseong
    email: kimwonseong@iiasa.ac.at
    affiliation: International Institute for Applied Systems Analysis (IIASA)
  - family-names: Erokhin
    given-names: Dmitry
    affiliation: International Institute for Applied Systems Analysis (IIASA)
repository-code: "https://github.com/Wonseong620/Causal_Network_Map"
url: "https://wonseong620.github.io/Causal_Network_Map/"
abstract: >-
  Interactive lead-lag network viewer and a curated replication package
  for a news-based sectoral shock-mapping framework applied to
  Iran-related hostilities. The package contains derived daily sectoral
  indicators and within-day share-transformed series by language,
  article-level sector-probability vectors (lexical TF-IDF and zero-shot
  LLM classifiers), full pairwise Toda-Yamamoto lead-lag edge tables with
  false-discovery-rate flags, the world-average input-output coefficient
  matrix and input-output alignment statistics, the 50-sector ICIO V1
  lookup, the LLM classification prompt, and all analysis and
  figure-generation scripts. Raw article text is not redistributed. Code
  is released under the MIT License; datasets under replication/data/ are
  released under CC BY 4.0.
keywords:
  - qualitative data
  - input-output analysis
  - geopolitical risk
  - production networks
  - text as data
  - shock indicators
license: MIT
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-07-08"
